
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class Bank {
  - name: String
}

class Customer {
  - firstName: String
  - lastName: String
}

class Branch {
  - name: String
}

class Account {
  - accountNumber: int
  - balance: double
}

class CurrentAccount {
  - overdraftLimit: double
}

class SavingsAccount {}

' Associations and relationships

Bank "1" *-- "0..*" Branch : has
Bank "1" *-- "0..*" Customer : manages
Customer "1" *-- "1..5" Account : owns
Account <|-- CurrentAccount
Account <|-- SavingsAccount

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **`Bank`** manages multiple **`Customer`s** and has multiple **`Branch`es**.
- Each **`Customer`** can have between 1 and 5 **`Account`s**.
- An **`Account`** has an `accountNumber`, `balance`.
- There are two types of accounts: **`CurrentAccount`** (with an `overdraftLimit`) and **`SavingsAccount`**, both inherit from **`Account`**.

